<content>
    <para id="id318968">This appendix contains outline proofs and derivations for the theorems and
formulas given in early part of <link target-id="m45100">Chapter: The Scaling Function and Scaling Coefficients, Wavelet and Wavelet Coefficients </link>.
They are not intended to be complete
or formal, but they should be sufficient to understand the ideas behind
why a result is true and to give some insight into its interpretation as
well as to indicate assumptions and restrictions.</para><para id="id318978"><emphasis effect="bold">Proof 1</emphasis><emphasis effect="italics"> The conditions given by <link target-id="uid20" document="m45100"/> and <link target-id="uid22" document="m45095"/> can be derived by
integrating both sides of</emphasis></para><equation id="uid2"><m:math overflow="scroll" mode="display">
        <m:mrow>
          <m:mi>φ</m:mi>
          <m:mrow>
            <m:mo>(</m:mo>
            <m:mi>x</m:mi>
            <m:mo>)</m:mo>
          </m:mrow>
          <m:mo>=</m:mo>
          <m:munder>
            <m:mo>∑</m:mo>
            <m:mi>n</m:mi>
          </m:munder>
          <m:mi>h</m:mi>
          <m:mrow>
            <m:mo>(</m:mo>
            <m:mi>n</m:mi>
            <m:mo>)</m:mo>
          </m:mrow>
          <m:mspace width="0.277778em"/>
          <m:msqrt>
            <m:mi>M</m:mi>
          </m:msqrt>
          <m:mspace width="0.166667em"/>
          <m:mi>φ</m:mi>
          <m:mrow>
            <m:mo>(</m:mo>
            <m:mi>M</m:mi>
            <m:mspace width="0.166667em"/>
            <m:mi>x</m:mi>
            <m:mo>-</m:mo>
            <m:mi>n</m:mi>
            <m:mo>)</m:mo>
          </m:mrow>
        </m:mrow>
      </m:math>
    </equation><para id="id319402"><emphasis effect="italics">and making the change of variables <m:math overflow="scroll"><m:mrow><m:mi>y</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mi>M</m:mi><m:mi>x</m:mi></m:mrow></m:math></emphasis></para><equation id="uid3">
      <m:math overflow="scroll" mode="display">
        <m:mrow>
          <m:mo>∫</m:mo>
          <m:mi>φ</m:mi>
          <m:mrow>
            <m:mo>(</m:mo>
            <m:mi>x</m:mi>
            <m:mo>)</m:mo>
          </m:mrow>
          <m:mspace width="0.166667em"/>
          <m:mi>d</m:mi>
          <m:mi>x</m:mi>
          <m:mo>=</m:mo>
          <m:munder>
            <m:mo>∑</m:mo>
            <m:mi>n</m:mi>
          </m:munder>
          <m:mi>h</m:mi>
          <m:mrow>
            <m:mo>(</m:mo>
            <m:mi>n</m:mi>
            <m:mo>)</m:mo>
          </m:mrow>
          <m:mo>∫</m:mo>
          <m:msqrt>
            <m:mi>M</m:mi>
          </m:msqrt>
          <m:mspace width="0.166667em"/>
          <m:mi>φ</m:mi>
          <m:mrow>
            <m:mo>(</m:mo>
            <m:mi>M</m:mi>
            <m:mi>x</m:mi>
            <m:mo>-</m:mo>
            <m:mi>n</m:mi>
            <m:mo>)</m:mo>
          </m:mrow>
          <m:mspace width="0.166667em"/>
          <m:mi>d</m:mi>
          <m:mi>x</m:mi>
        </m:mrow>
      </m:math>
    </equation>
    <para id="id319684"><emphasis effect="italics">and noting the integral is independent of translation which gives</emphasis></para><equation id="uid4">
      <m:math overflow="scroll" mode="display">
        <m:mrow>
          <m:mo>=</m:mo>
          <m:munder>
            <m:mo>∑</m:mo>
            <m:mi>n</m:mi>
          </m:munder>
          <m:mi>h</m:mi>
          <m:mrow>
            <m:mo>(</m:mo>
            <m:mi>n</m:mi>
            <m:mo>)</m:mo>
          </m:mrow>
          <m:mspace width="0.166667em"/>
          <m:msqrt>
            <m:mi>M</m:mi>
          </m:msqrt>
          <m:mspace width="0.166667em"/>
          <m:mo>∫</m:mo>
          <m:mi>φ</m:mi>
          <m:mrow>
            <m:mo>(</m:mo>
            <m:mi>y</m:mi>
            <m:mo>)</m:mo>
          </m:mrow>
          <m:mfrac>
            <m:mn>1</m:mn>
            <m:mi>M</m:mi>
          </m:mfrac>
          <m:mspace width="0.166667em"/>
          <m:mi>d</m:mi>
          <m:mi>y</m:mi>
          <m:mo>.</m:mo>
        </m:mrow>
      </m:math>
    </equation>
    <para id="id319758"><emphasis effect="italics">With no further requirements other than <m:math overflow="scroll"><m:mrow><m:mi>φ</m:mi><m:mo>∈</m:mo><m:msup><m:mi>L</m:mi><m:mn>1</m:mn></m:msup></m:mrow></m:math>
to allow the sum and integral interchange and <m:math overflow="scroll"><m:mrow><m:mo>∫</m:mo><m:mi>φ</m:mi><m:mo>(</m:mo><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>)</m:mo><m:mspace width="0.166667em"/><m:mi>d</m:mi><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>≠</m:mo><m:mn>0</m:mn></m:mrow></m:math>, this gives <link target-id="uid22" document="m45095"/> as</emphasis></para><equation id="uid5">
      <m:math overflow="scroll" mode="display">
        <m:mrow>
          <m:munder>
            <m:mo>∑</m:mo>
            <m:mi>n</m:mi>
          </m:munder>
          <m:mi>h</m:mi>
          <m:mrow>
            <m:mo>(</m:mo>
            <m:mi>n</m:mi>
            <m:mo>)</m:mo>
          </m:mrow>
          <m:mo>=</m:mo>
          <m:msqrt>
            <m:mi>M</m:mi>
          </m:msqrt>
        </m:mrow>
      </m:math>
    </equation>
    <para id="id319849"><emphasis effect="italics">and for <m:math overflow="scroll"><m:mrow><m:mi>M</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>2</m:mn></m:mrow></m:math> gives <link target-id="uid20" document="m45100"/>. Note this does not assume
orthogonality nor any specific normalization of <m:math overflow="scroll"><m:mrow><m:mi>φ</m:mi><m:mo>(</m:mo><m:mi>t</m:mi><m:mo>)</m:mo></m:mrow></m:math> and does not
even assume <m:math overflow="scroll"><m:mi>M</m:mi></m:math> is an integer.</emphasis></para><para id="id319894">This is the most basic necessary condition for the existence of
<m:math overflow="scroll"><m:mrow><m:mi>φ</m:mi><m:mo>(</m:mo><m:mi>t</m:mi><m:mo>)</m:mo></m:mrow></m:math> and it has the fewest assumptions or restrictions.</para>
    <para id="id319913"><emphasis effect="bold">Proof 2</emphasis><emphasis effect="italics"> The conditions in <link target-id="uid26" document="m45100"/> and <link target-id="uid24" document="m45095"/> are a down-sampled
orthogonality of translates by <m:math overflow="scroll"><m:mi>M</m:mi></m:math> of the coefficients which results from
the orthogonality of translates of the scaling function given by</emphasis></para><equation id="uid7">
      <m:math overflow="scroll" mode="display">
        <m:mrow>
          <m:mo>∫</m:mo>
          <m:mi>φ</m:mi>
          <m:mo>(</m:mo>
          <m:mi>x</m:mi>
          <m:mo>)</m:mo>
          <m:mspace width="0.166667em"/>
          <m:mi>φ</m:mi>
          <m:mo>(</m:mo>
          <m:mi>x</m:mi>
          <m:mo>-</m:mo>
          <m:mi>m</m:mi>
          <m:mo>)</m:mo>
          <m:mspace width="0.166667em"/>
          <m:mi>d</m:mi>
          <m:mi>x</m:mi>
          <m:mo>=</m:mo>
          <m:mi>E</m:mi>
          <m:mspace width="0.166667em"/>
          <m:mi>δ</m:mi>
          <m:mo>(</m:mo>
          <m:mi>m</m:mi>
          <m:mo>)</m:mo>
        </m:mrow>
      </m:math>
    </equation>
    <para id="id320001"><emphasis effect="italics">in <link target-id=""/>. The basic scaling equation <link target-id="uid2"/> is substituted for
both functions in <link target-id="uid7"/> giving</emphasis></para><equation id="uid8">
      <m:math overflow="scroll" mode="display">
        <m:mrow>
          <m:mo>∫</m:mo>
          <m:mfenced separators="" open="[" close="]">
            <m:munder>
              <m:mo>∑</m:mo>
              <m:mi>n</m:mi>
            </m:munder>
            <m:mi>h</m:mi>
            <m:mrow>
              <m:mo>(</m:mo>
              <m:mi>n</m:mi>
              <m:mo>)</m:mo>
            </m:mrow>
            <m:mspace width="0.166667em"/>
            <m:msqrt>
              <m:mi>M</m:mi>
            </m:msqrt>
            <m:mspace width="0.166667em"/>
            <m:mi>φ</m:mi>
            <m:mrow>
              <m:mo>(</m:mo>
              <m:mi>M</m:mi>
              <m:mi>x</m:mi>
              <m:mo>-</m:mo>
              <m:mi>n</m:mi>
              <m:mo>)</m:mo>
            </m:mrow>
          </m:mfenced>
          <m:mfenced separators="" open="[" close="]">
            <m:munder>
              <m:mo>∑</m:mo>
              <m:mi>k</m:mi>
            </m:munder>
            <m:mi>h</m:mi>
            <m:mrow>
              <m:mo>(</m:mo>
              <m:mi>k</m:mi>
              <m:mo>)</m:mo>
            </m:mrow>
            <m:mspace width="0.166667em"/>
            <m:msqrt>
              <m:mi>M</m:mi>
            </m:msqrt>
            <m:mspace width="0.166667em"/>
            <m:mi>φ</m:mi>
            <m:mrow>
              <m:mo>(</m:mo>
              <m:mi>M</m:mi>
              <m:mi>x</m:mi>
              <m:mo>-</m:mo>
              <m:mi>M</m:mi>
              <m:mi>m</m:mi>
              <m:mo>-</m:mo>
              <m:mi>k</m:mi>
              <m:mo>)</m:mo>
            </m:mrow>
          </m:mfenced>
          <m:mspace width="0.166667em"/>
          <m:mi>d</m:mi>
          <m:mi>x</m:mi>
          <m:mo>=</m:mo>
          <m:mi>E</m:mi>
          <m:mspace width="0.166667em"/>
          <m:mi>δ</m:mi>
          <m:mrow>
            <m:mo>(</m:mo>
            <m:mi>m</m:mi>
            <m:mo>)</m:mo>
          </m:mrow>
        </m:mrow>
      </m:math>
    </equation>
    <para id="id320162"><emphasis effect="italics">which, after reordering and a change of variable <m:math overflow="scroll"><m:mrow><m:mi>y</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mi>M</m:mi><m:mspace width="0.166667em"/><m:mi>x</m:mi></m:mrow></m:math>, gives</emphasis></para><equation id="uid9">
      <m:math overflow="scroll" mode="display">
        <m:mrow>
          <m:munder>
            <m:mo>∑</m:mo>
            <m:mi>n</m:mi>
          </m:munder>
          <m:munder>
            <m:mo>∑</m:mo>
            <m:mi>k</m:mi>
          </m:munder>
          <m:mi>h</m:mi>
          <m:mrow>
            <m:mo>(</m:mo>
            <m:mi>n</m:mi>
            <m:mo>)</m:mo>
          </m:mrow>
          <m:mspace width="0.166667em"/>
          <m:mi>h</m:mi>
          <m:mrow>
            <m:mo>(</m:mo>
            <m:mi>k</m:mi>
            <m:mo>)</m:mo>
          </m:mrow>
          <m:mo>∫</m:mo>
          <m:mi>φ</m:mi>
          <m:mrow>
            <m:mo>(</m:mo>
            <m:mi>y</m:mi>
            <m:mo>-</m:mo>
            <m:mi>n</m:mi>
            <m:mo>)</m:mo>
          </m:mrow>
          <m:mspace width="0.166667em"/>
          <m:mi>φ</m:mi>
          <m:mrow>
            <m:mo>(</m:mo>
            <m:mi>y</m:mi>
            <m:mo>-</m:mo>
            <m:mi>M</m:mi>
            <m:mi>m</m:mi>
            <m:mo>-</m:mo>
            <m:mi>k</m:mi>
            <m:mo>)</m:mo>
          </m:mrow>
          <m:mspace width="0.166667em"/>
          <m:mi>d</m:mi>
          <m:mi>y</m:mi>
          <m:mo>=</m:mo>
          <m:mi>E</m:mi>
          <m:mspace width="0.166667em"/>
          <m:mi>δ</m:mi>
          <m:mrow>
            <m:mo>(</m:mo>
            <m:mi>m</m:mi>
            <m:mo>)</m:mo>
          </m:mrow>
          <m:mo>.</m:mo>
        </m:mrow>
      </m:math>
    </equation>
    <para id="id320302"><emphasis effect="italics">Using the orthogonality in <link target-id="uid7"/> gives our result</emphasis></para><equation id="uid10">
      <m:math overflow="scroll" mode="display">
        <m:mrow>
          <m:munder>
            <m:mo>∑</m:mo>
            <m:mi>n</m:mi>
          </m:munder>
          <m:mi>h</m:mi>
          <m:mrow>
            <m:mo>(</m:mo>
            <m:mi>n</m:mi>
            <m:mo>)</m:mo>
          </m:mrow>
          <m:mspace width="0.166667em"/>
          <m:mi>h</m:mi>
          <m:mrow>
            <m:mo>(</m:mo>
            <m:mi>n</m:mi>
            <m:mo>-</m:mo>
            <m:mi>M</m:mi>
            <m:mi>m</m:mi>
            <m:mo>)</m:mo>
          </m:mrow>
          <m:mspace width="0.277778em"/>
          <m:mo>=</m:mo>
          <m:mspace width="0.277778em"/>
          <m:mi>δ</m:mi>
          <m:mrow>
            <m:mo>(</m:mo>
            <m:mi>m</m:mi>
            <m:mo>)</m:mo>
          </m:mrow>
        </m:mrow>
      </m:math>
    </equation>
    <para id="id320378"><emphasis effect="italics">in <link target-id="uid25" document="m45100"/> and <link target-id="uid24" document="m45095"/>. This result requires the orthogonality
condition <link target-id="uid7"/>, <m:math overflow="scroll"><m:mi>M</m:mi></m:math> must be an integer, and any non-zero
normalization <m:math overflow="scroll"><m:mi>E</m:mi></m:math> may be used.</emphasis></para><!--empty paragraphs get left behind.-->
    <para id="id320414"><emphasis effect="bold">Proof 3 (Corollary 2)</emphasis> <emphasis effect="italics">
The result that</emphasis></para><equation id="uid12">
      <m:math overflow="scroll" mode="display">
        <m:mrow>
          <m:munder>
            <m:mo>∑</m:mo>
            <m:mi>n</m:mi>
          </m:munder>
          <m:mi>h</m:mi>
          <m:mrow>
            <m:mo>(</m:mo>
            <m:mn>2</m:mn>
            <m:mi>n</m:mi>
            <m:mo>)</m:mo>
          </m:mrow>
          <m:mo>=</m:mo>
          <m:munder>
            <m:mo>∑</m:mo>
            <m:mi>n</m:mi>
          </m:munder>
          <m:mi>h</m:mi>
          <m:mrow>
            <m:mo>(</m:mo>
            <m:mn>2</m:mn>
            <m:mi>n</m:mi>
            <m:mo>+</m:mo>
            <m:mn>1</m:mn>
            <m:mo>)</m:mo>
          </m:mrow>
          <m:mo>=</m:mo>
          <m:mn>1</m:mn>
          <m:mo>/</m:mo>
          <m:msqrt>
            <m:mn>2</m:mn>
          </m:msqrt>
        </m:mrow>
      </m:math>
    </equation>
    <para id="id320493"><emphasis effect="italics">in <link target-id="uid31" document="m45100"/> or, more generally</emphasis></para><equation id="uid13">
      <m:math overflow="scroll" mode="display">
        <m:mrow>
          <m:munder>
            <m:mo>∑</m:mo>
            <m:mi>n</m:mi>
          </m:munder>
          <m:mi>h</m:mi>
          <m:mrow>
            <m:mo>(</m:mo>
            <m:mi>M</m:mi>
            <m:mspace width="0.166667em"/>
            <m:mi>n</m:mi>
            <m:mo>)</m:mo>
          </m:mrow>
          <m:mo>=</m:mo>
          <m:munder>
            <m:mo>∑</m:mo>
            <m:mi>n</m:mi>
          </m:munder>
          <m:mi>h</m:mi>
          <m:mrow>
            <m:mo>(</m:mo>
            <m:mi>M</m:mi>
            <m:mspace width="0.166667em"/>
            <m:mi>n</m:mi>
            <m:mo>+</m:mo>
            <m:mi>k</m:mi>
            <m:mo>)</m:mo>
          </m:mrow>
          <m:mo>=</m:mo>
          <m:mn>1</m:mn>
          <m:mo>/</m:mo>
          <m:msqrt>
            <m:mi>M</m:mi>
          </m:msqrt>
        </m:mrow>
      </m:math>
    </equation>
    <para id="id320573"><emphasis effect="italics">is obtained by breaking <link target-id="uid5"/> for <m:math overflow="scroll"><m:mrow><m:mi>M</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>2</m:mn></m:mrow></m:math> into the sum of the even and
odd coefficients.</emphasis></para><equation id="uid14">
      <m:math overflow="scroll" mode="display">
        <m:mrow>
          <m:munder>
            <m:mo>∑</m:mo>
            <m:mi>n</m:mi>
          </m:munder>
          <m:mi>h</m:mi>
          <m:mrow>
            <m:mo>(</m:mo>
            <m:mi>n</m:mi>
            <m:mo>)</m:mo>
          </m:mrow>
          <m:mo>=</m:mo>
          <m:munder>
            <m:mo>∑</m:mo>
            <m:mi>k</m:mi>
          </m:munder>
          <m:mi>h</m:mi>
          <m:mrow>
            <m:mo>(</m:mo>
            <m:mn>2</m:mn>
            <m:mi>k</m:mi>
            <m:mo>)</m:mo>
          </m:mrow>
          <m:mo>+</m:mo>
          <m:munder>
            <m:mo>∑</m:mo>
            <m:mi>k</m:mi>
          </m:munder>
          <m:mi>h</m:mi>
          <m:mrow>
            <m:mo>(</m:mo>
            <m:mn>2</m:mn>
            <m:mi>k</m:mi>
            <m:mo>+</m:mo>
            <m:mn>1</m:mn>
            <m:mo>)</m:mo>
          </m:mrow>
          <m:mo>=</m:mo>
          <m:msub>
            <m:mi>K</m:mi>
            <m:mn>0</m:mn>
          </m:msub>
          <m:mo>+</m:mo>
          <m:msub>
            <m:mi>K</m:mi>
            <m:mn>1</m:mn>
          </m:msub>
          <m:mo>=</m:mo>
          <m:msqrt>
            <m:mn>2</m:mn>
          </m:msqrt>
          <m:mo>.</m:mo>
        </m:mrow>
      </m:math>
    </equation>
    <para id="id320700"><emphasis effect="italics">Next we use <link target-id="uid10"/> and sum over <m:math overflow="scroll"><m:mi>n</m:mi></m:math> to give</emphasis></para><equation id="uid15">
      <m:math overflow="scroll" mode="display">
        <m:mrow>
          <m:munder>
            <m:mo>∑</m:mo>
            <m:mi>n</m:mi>
          </m:munder>
          <m:munder>
            <m:mo>∑</m:mo>
            <m:mi>k</m:mi>
          </m:munder>
          <m:mi>h</m:mi>
          <m:mrow>
            <m:mo>(</m:mo>
            <m:mi>k</m:mi>
            <m:mo>+</m:mo>
            <m:mn>2</m:mn>
            <m:mi>n</m:mi>
            <m:mo>)</m:mo>
          </m:mrow>
          <m:mi>h</m:mi>
          <m:mrow>
            <m:mo>(</m:mo>
            <m:mi>k</m:mi>
            <m:mo>)</m:mo>
          </m:mrow>
          <m:mo>=</m:mo>
          <m:mn>1</m:mn>
        </m:mrow>
      </m:math>
    </equation>
    <para id="id320775"><emphasis effect="italics">which we then split into even and odd sums and reorder to give:</emphasis></para><equation id="id320781"><m:math overflow="scroll" mode="display">
   <m:mtable>
    <m:mtd>
     <m:mtr>   

     <m:mrow>
          <m:munder>
            <m:mo>∑</m:mo>
            <m:mi>n</m:mi>
          </m:munder>
          <m:mfenced separators="" open="[" close="]">
            <m:munder>
              <m:mo>∑</m:mo>
              <m:mi>k</m:mi>
            </m:munder>
            <m:mi>h</m:mi>
            <m:mrow>
              <m:mo>(</m:mo>
              <m:mn>2</m:mn>
              <m:mi>k</m:mi>
              <m:mo>+</m:mo>
              <m:mn>2</m:mn>
              <m:mi>n</m:mi>
              <m:mo>)</m:mo>
            </m:mrow>
            <m:mi>h</m:mi>
            <m:mrow>
              <m:mo>(</m:mo>
              <m:mn>2</m:mn>
              <m:mi>k</m:mi>
              <m:mo>)</m:mo>
            </m:mrow>
            <m:mo>+</m:mo>
            <m:munder>
