    <para id="id326310"><emphasis effect="italics">But the integral on the right hand side is <m:math overflow="scroll"><m:msub><m:mi>A</m:mi><m:mn>0</m:mn></m:msub></m:math>, usually normalized to
one and from <link target-id="uid31" document="m45100"/> or <link target-id="uid12"/> and <link target-id="uid55"/> we know that</emphasis></para><equation id="uid58">
